[src:fft-algorithm/number-theoretic-transform] As above, we may extend the base field to $\mathrm {GF} (q)$ in order to find a primitive root, i.e. a splitting field for $x^{n}-1$ .
[src:fft-algorithm/number-theoretic-transform] When $p|n$ , we may still define an $F_{p}$ -linear isomorphism as above.
[src:fft-algorithm/number-theoretic-transform] The modules occurring are now indecomposable rather than irreducible.
